 {"id":"bd-1e50","title":"P6.9: Implement detailed test logging for debugging failures","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T21:40:14.962143148Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-19T21:42:30.625340753Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1e50","depends_on_id":"bd-xfp9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-19T21:40:41.207634554Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":56,"issue_id":"bd-1e50","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"## Task: Implement detailed test logging for debugging failures

### What to Do

Create a test logging infrastructure that captures detailed information when tests fail, making debugging faster and easier.

### Problem

When tests fail in CI, you often get minimal output like:
```
test output_tests::denial_box_renders ... FAILED
assertion failed: expected != actual
```

This makes debugging nearly impossible without running locally.

### Solution: Rich Test Logging

```rust
// tests/support/logging.rs

use std::sync::Once;
use tracing_subscriber::{EnvFilter, fmt};

static INIT: Once = Once::new();

/// Initialize test logging. Call at the start of each test module.
pub fn init_test_logging() {
    INIT.call_once(|| {
        let filter = EnvFilter::try_from_default_env()
            .unwrap_or_else(|_| EnvFilter::new("dcg=debug,test=debug"));

        fmt()
            .with_env_filter(filter)
            .with_test_writer()  // Capture in test output
            .with_file(true)
            .with_line_number(true)
            .with_target(true)
            .init();
    });
}

/// Log test context for debugging
#[macro_export]
macro_rules! test_context {
    ($($arg:tt)*) => {
        tracing::info!(target: "test", $($arg)*);
    };
}

/// Capture and log a value for debugging
pub fn debug_capture<T: std::fmt::Debug>(name: &str, value: T) -> T {
    tracing::debug!(target: "test", "{} = {:?}", name, &value);
    value
}
```

### Usage in Tests

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use crate::tests::support::logging::{init_test_logging, debug_capture};

    #[test]
    fn denial_box_renders_correctly() {
        init_test_logging();
        test_context!("Starting denial_box_renders_correctly");

        let denial = debug_capture("denial", DenialBox {
            command: "rm -rf /".to_string(),
            reason: "Dangerous".to_string(),
            ..Default::default()
        });

        let theme = debug_capture("theme", Theme::default());
        let output = debug_capture("output", denial.render(&theme));

        test_context!("Checking output contains command");
        assert!(output.contains("rm -rf /"), 
            "Output missing command.\nExpected to contain: 'rm -rf /'\nActual output:\n{}",
            output
        );
    }
}
```

### Enhanced Assertion Macros

```rust
/// Assert with detailed diff on failure
#[macro_export]
macro_rules! assert_output_eq {
    ($expected:expr, $actual:expr) => {
        if $expected != $actual {
            let diff = similar::TextDiff::from_lines(&$expected, &$actual);
            let mut diff_output = String::new();
            for change in diff.iter_all_changes() {
                let sign = match change.tag() {
                    similar::ChangeTag::Delete => "-",
                    similar::ChangeTag::Insert => "+",
                    similar::ChangeTag::Equal => " ",
                };
                diff_output.push_str(&format!("{}{}", sign, change));
            }
            panic!(
                "Output mismatch:\n\
                 === EXPECTED ===\n{}\n\
                 === ACTUAL ===\n{}\n\
                 === DIFF ===\n{}",
                $expected, $actual, diff_output
            );
        }
    };
}
```

### CI Configuration for Verbose Output

```yaml
# .github/workflows/test.yml
- name: Run tests with verbose logging
  run: |
    RUST_LOG=dcg=debug,test=debug cargo test --features rich-output -- --nocapture 2>&1 | tee test_output.log

- name: Upload test logs on failure
  if: failure()
  uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
  with:
    name: test-logs
    path: test_output.log
```

### Test Output Artifacts

On failure, capture:
1. Full test output with tracing
2. Any rendered output (save to file)
3. Environment variables
4. Cargo features enabled
5. Git commit hash

```rust
fn save_failure_artifact(test_name: &str, output: &str) {
    let path = format!("target/test-artifacts/{}.txt", test_name);
    std::fs::create_dir_all("target/test-artifacts").ok();
    std::fs::write(&path, output).ok();
    eprintln!("Saved failure artifact to: {}", path);
}
```
